                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-59-off331 t18300415-59-crimeloc333"></join>. On the 6th of April the prisoner's father came and asked if I would take the prisoner as a lodger, which I did - he slept in my room; I went out between two and three o'clock in the afternoon - I came back a quarter before seven, and he was gone; my drawer was unlocked, and the coat and waistcoat were gone, also three shoes; I met him, and took him, but the property has not been found.</p>
